<div class="homework">
  
<section>
  <h2>Homework 2: Definition of Probability</h2>

  <ol>
    <li> Section 1.5, #3, 4, 7. 
    </li>

    <li>
      Assume that \(P(A\cap B) = 0.3\), \(P(A\cap C) = 0.4\),
      \(P(B\cap C) = 0.3\), \(P(A^c\cap B^c\cap C) = 0\), \(P(C)= 0.6\),
      \(P(A\cup C) = 0.8\), and \(P(B^c\cup C) = 0.7\).
      <ol class="nested-list">
         <li>Fill in all of the probabilities in the Venn diagram for
	   \(A\), \(B\), and \(C\).</li>
	 <li> Find \(P(B^c)\), \(P(A\cap B\cap C)\), and \(P(A)\).</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
  </ol>

</section>

